From 6a3d6b12be62c5bcf5853665e5d7de33ec707863 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 22:20:48 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 157/174] x86/mm: PGCL: PAGE-align the realmode-trampoline W+X
 suppression range

note_wx() suppresses the (intentional) trampoline W+X warning under
PAGE_MMUSHIFT>0, but bounded the suppressed range by
[real_mode_header, real_mode_header + PAGE_ALIGN(blob_size)].  The
trampoline is only MMUPAGE-aligned -- reserve_real_mode() allocates with
MMUPAGE_SIZE alignment because a PAGE_SIZE (e.g. 256K) alignment is
unsatisfiable in a fragmented sub-1M e820 -- while
set_real_mode_permissions() clears NX on the whole PAGE_SIZE page(s) via
set_memory_x(__va(PAGE_ALIGN_DOWN(text_start))).  The resulting W+X run
therefore begins at the PAGE boundary *below* real_mode_header, so
ptdump's start_address < rm_base, the `start_address >= rm_base` test
fails, and the warning fires anyway.

Observed on the laptop's real (fragmented) e820: trampoline blob at phys
0x90000 (MMUPAGE/64K-aligned); with a 256K PAGE the W+X run lands at
__va(0x80000) = 0xffff888000080000, below real_mode_header = __va(0x90000).
Both pgcl6 (#16) and pgcl4 (#17) hit it; QEMU's contiguous low memory
happens to place the trampoline PAGE-aligned, so the matrix never saw it.

PAGE-align the suppression range to cover exactly the page(s) that
set_memory_x() marks.  Gated on PAGE_MMUSHIFT>0; identity at
PAGE_MMUSHIFT==0 (the trampoline is PAGE-aligned there).  dump_pagetables.o
compile-verified at PGCL=6; laptop-boot reconfirmation pending (not
reproducible under QEMU).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/x86/mm/dump_pagetables.c | 17 ++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/mm/dump_pagetables.c b/arch/x86/mm/dump_pagetables.c
index 139209ef3191..5924e816b6b2 100644
--- a/arch/x86/mm/dump_pagetables.c
+++ b/arch/x86/mm/dump_pagetables.c
@@ -249,9 +249,20 @@ static void note_wx(struct pg_state *st, unsigned long addr)
 	 * is intentionally W+X.  Suppress the warning.
 	 */
 	if (PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0 && real_mode_header) {
-		unsigned long rm_base = (unsigned long)real_mode_header;
-		unsigned long rm_end = rm_base +
-			PAGE_ALIGN(real_mode_blob_end - real_mode_blob);
+		/*
+		 * The trampoline is only MMUPAGE-aligned (a PAGE_SIZE alignment
+		 * is unsatisfiable in a fragmented sub-1M e820), but
+		 * set_real_mode_permissions() clears NX on the whole PAGE_SIZE
+		 * page(s) containing it via set_memory_x(PAGE_ALIGN_DOWN(...)).
+		 * The resulting W+X run therefore begins at the PAGE boundary
+		 * *below* real_mode_header, so the suppression range must be
+		 * PAGE-aligned to actually cover it.
+		 */
+		unsigned long rm_base =
+			PAGE_ALIGN_DOWN((unsigned long)real_mode_header);
+		unsigned long rm_end =
+			PAGE_ALIGN((unsigned long)real_mode_header +
+				   (real_mode_blob_end - real_mode_blob));
 
 		if (st->start_address >= rm_base &&
 		    addr <= rm_end) {
-- 
